# EKET CODEOWNERS
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-configuration/about-code-owners
#
# Any change to perf baselines or CI gates requires an owner review.
# Owners are placeholder GitHub handles — replace before enabling branch protection.

# Performance baseline: must be deliberate, reviewer-approved bump.
/benchmarks/baseline.json         @eket-perf-owners

# CI gates: changing these can silently weaken the pipeline.
/.github/workflows/dual-engine.yml    @eket-ci-owners
/.github/workflows/perf-baseline.yml  @eket-ci-owners @eket-perf-owners
/.github/workflows/debrief-check.yml  @eket-ci-owners

# Dual-engine framework: equivalence guarantees live here.
/tests/dual-engine/                   @eket-platform-owners

# State writers / schemas: changes here affect byte-equivalence.
/lib/state/                           @eket-platform-owners
/node/src/core/state/                 @eket-platform-owners
/protocol/                            @eket-platform-owners

# Master/Slaver role rules: governance, not code.
/template/docs/MASTER-*.md            @eket-governance-owners
/template/docs/SLAVER-*.md            @eket-governance-owners
/template/docs/EXPERT-PANEL-*.md      @eket-governance-owners
